<head type="main">LIBERTY.</head>
<lg type="poem">
<l>SAY, What is Freedom? What the right of souls</l>
<l>Which all who know are bound to keep, or die,</l>
<l>And who knows not, is dead? In vain ye pry</l>
<l>In musty archives, or retentive scrolls,</l>
<l>Charters and statues, constitutions, rolls,</l>
<l>And remnants of the old world's history:&#38;</l>
<l>These show what has been, not what ought to be,</l>
<l>Or teach at best how wiser Time controuls</l>
<l>Man's futile purposes. As vain the search</l>
<l>Of restless factions, who, in lawless will,</l>
<l>Fix the foundations of a creedless church&#38;</l>
<l>A lawless rule&#38;an anarchy of ill:</l>
<l>But what is Freedom? Rightly understood,</l>
<l>A unviersal license to be good.</l>
</lg>
